3.20	Bryan_Adams_discography	Bryan Adams discography	The discography of Canadian recording artist Bryan Adams consists of ten studio albums, five compilation albums, two soundtrack albums, four live albums and sixty-seven singles. After the success of his debut single, "Let Me Take You Dancing" (1979), Adams signed a recording contract with A&amp;M Records. Bryan Adams (1980), his debut album, peaked at number 69 on the Canadian RPM Albums Chart. Adams followed this with You Want It You Got It (1981), which peaked at number 118 on the Billboard 200 and was certified gold in Canada. Cuts Like a Knife, his third release, became his first successful work outside Canada. The album charted within the top ten in Canada and the United States and was certified three-times platinum by the Canadian Recording Industry Association (CRIA) and platinum by the Recording Industry Association of America (RIAA). Reckless (1984), his fourth studio album, selling between eight to twelve million copies worldwide and featured the hit singles "Run to You", "Heaven" and "Summer of '69". In 1987, he released Into the Fire, which reached platinum status in the United States and triple-platinum in Canada.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1d/Flickr_Bryan_Adams_in_Peterborough_2009_%2807%29.jpg/250px-Flickr_Bryan_Adams_in_Peterborough_2009_%2807%29.jpg
